results.name: Decimal expansion of the real part of psi(i), i being the imaginary unit.
comment: For real b, Im(psi(b*i)) = 1/(2*b) + Pi*coth(Pi*b)/2, but no such closed formula is known for the real part (see Wikipedia link). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Dec 24 2020
link: Stanislav Sykora, Table of n, a(n) for n = -1..2000
formula: psi(i) = -EulerGamma - Sum_{k>=0} ((k-1)/(k+1)/(k^2+1)) + A113319*i, where EulerGamma is the Euler-Mascheroni constant (A001620).
results.author: _Stanislav Sykora_, Oct 03 2014
